data.text:
Post by George Tropicana on

You may remember Aselin Debison, the young girl with the big voice, who released her stunning debut album "Sweet Is The Melody" in September 2002.

Now she's 14 and she's back with a singer-songwriter sound. Check out "Life" and its video at www.aselin.com

It looks like one of the videos Sean (computerfreak) would like! She looks like JoJo now too!

"Life" sounds nice enough of a rock/pop song.. but what happened to that "special voice" which captured my attention back in 2002?

--

Watch the video: www.sonymusic.ca/cgi-bin/Canada/stream.cgi?file=Canada/AselinDebison/Life_hi.wmv

EDIT: On second listen, I really like it. The video, mature lyrics, and melody fit together so well. No disrespect to JoJo, Raven, and Hilary Duff, but I would really be happy to see a positive image like Aselin shown on music video channels. This is what many young adults go through, trying to discover who they are and learn what "life" is about.

Post by George Tropicana on
